n price panel (bhavcopy-reconstructed) + NSE index TR + bhavcopy turnover.","frequency":"daily","confidence":"high where history is long; flagged low if thin/short.","why_useful":"what the market is saying about the stock \u2014 trend, leadership vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":true,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":71.1,"unit":"/100","status":"good","read":"High-quality business (71/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":null,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"na","read":null,"meaning":"Operating cash flow is not a meaningful concept for a lender (deposits & loans dominate the cash statement).","why_useful":"For banks, earnings quality is read from asset quality / provisioning instead (not in MVP-1).","why_it_can_fail":null},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":null,"unit":"","status":"na","read":null,"meaning":"A bank is structurally levered (deposits are its raw material); D/E & interest-cover don't apply.","why_useful":"Read bank safety from capital adequacy (CAR) and NPAs instead (not in MVP-1).","why_it_can_fail":null},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":34.22,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 34% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-o